TY  - JOUR
TI  - The Stability of a Competitive Economy: A Survey Article
AU  - Negishi, Takashi
AB  - [Some of the recent contributions to the problem of the stability of a competitive economy are surveyed. Emphases are laid on the uses of economic laws such as Walras' law, the homogeneity of demand functions with respect to prices, etc., in proving stability, and on the development of models of nontâtonnement processes of adjustment in the market.]
C1  - Full publication date: Oct., 1962
DB  - JSTOR
